BP Solar, a unit of energy giant BP, will construct a groundbreaking solar plant in Alentejo, creating 240 jobs.
With 350,000 solar panels spread over 114 hectares, the plant will produce 62 megawatts, surpassing Germany's largest station.
The project aligns with Portugal's renewable energy goals under the Kyoto Protocol.
Meanwhile, solar-powered car races in Australia showcase innovative technology.
In the Philippines, a solar power project aims to electrify rural villages.
Taiwan also shows promise in solar energy development.
The solar industry's growth is attracting investors, signaling a shift towards sustainable energy sources worldwide.
